A glass of milk is 8 ounces of milk. Jo.content:
John drinks 2 glasses of milk, with each glass being 8 ounces. Therefore, the total volume of milk consumed is:
\[
2 \text{ glasses} \times 8 \text{ ounces per glass} = 16 \text{ ounces}
\]
Given that milk contains 3 calories per ounce, the total number of calories consumed is:
\[
16 \text{ ounces} \times 3 \text{ calories per ounce} = 48 \text{ calories}
\]

\boxed{48}
